2n+1<2^n
n\ge3
P(3)
2k+1<2^k
k\in \mathbb{N}\setminus\{1,2\}
2(k+1)+1<2^{k+1}
2
2\cdot(2k+1)<2^{k+1}
2(k+1)+1=2k+2+1<2k+2+2k=4k+2
P(n): 2^n>2n+1
n=2,2^2=4,2\cdot2+1=5
P(2)
n=3,2^3=8,2\cdot3+1=7\implies P(n)
n=3
P(n)
n=m\implies 2^m>2m+1
\implies 2^{m+1}=2(2^m)>2(2m+1)=4m+2
P(m+1)
2^{m+1}>2(m+1)+1=2m+3
4m+2>2(m+1)+1
2m>1\iff m\ge1
